{
  "name": "leios_voter_votes_two_ebs",
  "description": "Voter 5 votes for EB1 (slot=100, hash=ab...) in the first batch, then for EB2 (slot=101, hash=cd...) in the second batch. These are two distinct endorsement blocks so both votes are legitimate \u2014 each voter is entitled to cast one vote per EB. A node that deduplicates by voter_id alone, rather than the full (voter_id, slot, eb_hash) triple, will incorrectly discard voter 5's vote for EB2 as a duplicate of their EB1 vote. This is the false-positive failure mode of a naive deduplication implementation: it silently under-counts the vote tally for EB2, causing a correctly-voted EB to fail a threshold check it should have passed. A conforming node must accept both votes from voter 5 and count them toward their respective EBs.",
  "network_magic": 42,
  "trace_output_path": "trace_leios_voter_votes_two_ebs.jsonl",
  "expected_outcome": "success",
